<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-018-742  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 018 742.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EXE  Nov 1989 v4 n6 p8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Process Communications Ltd. (England) 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Multiscope. (debugging tool for use with OS-2 Multiscope)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Logitech Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     DebuggingCompatible SoftwareCompilersModula-2.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MultiscopeandM;Logitech, the US company best-known for its Modula-2 compiler, has devised anew debugging tool for use with OS/2.andP;  MultiScope is compatible withCodeView, so you can use it to debug programs generated by Microsoftcompilers.andP;  There is source code and expression evaluation support for C,Pascal and assembly language, as well as Logitech Modula-2.andP;  The compilerruns in text mode or under PM and performs most of the tricks expected frommodern debuggers: remote debugging via a serial port, ability to drive asecond monitor, multiple windows showing different kinds of information andso on.andM;One feature that I have not previously encountered is MultiScope's postmortem system.andP;  The idea is that when your application crashes, it writes outa file recording the state of the program when it fell over.andP;  The debuggercan then read and interpret the file.andP;  This facility can be added to programsrun outside the debugger; for example it could be applied to beta testcopies, enabling testers to return precise information about bugs.andM;MultiScope requires OS/2V1.1 or above.andP;  It costs 299 pound sterling ex VATand is available now.andP;  It is distributed in the UK by QA Training (0285655888).andO;</TEXT></DOC>